Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read the Prime Minister’s address for the latest information.

Pitcairn Island has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Pitcairn Island, see Return to the UK
To comply with local working practices regarding coronavirus (COVID-19), before embarkation all arriving vessels must establish contact with immigration and speak directly to Pitcairn’s doctor to check if any passengers have recently travelled to China and if any have respiratory symptoms.
